# **Personal Expense Tracker Backend**

This repository contains the backend service for the **Personal Expense Tracker App**, built with **Node.js** and following a modular architecture for scalability and maintainability.

---

## **Features**

- **User Authentication**:
  - User registration and login with **JWT-based authentication**.
  - Secure password storage with **bcrypt**.
- **Expense Management**:
  - Create, update, delete, and retrieve expenses.
  - Set expense limits and track progress.
- **Category Management**:
  - Create, edit, and delete expense categories.
- **Notifications**:
  - Notify users when they are nearing or exceeding their expense limits.
- **Scalable and Maintainable Architecture**:
  - Modular design with separate layers for routes, controllers, services, and utilities.

---


---

## **Technologies Used**

- **Backend Framework**: Node.js with Express.js
- **Database**: MongoDB (with Mongoose ODM)
- **Authentication**: JSON Web Tokens (JWT)
- **Password Security**: bcrypt.js
- **Environment Management**: dotenv
- **Testing Framework**: (Jest)
---

## **Setup and Installation**

1. **Clone the Repository**:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/minurawijesinghe/SIT725-group-project.git
   cd SIT725-group-project
   npm install

## **Set Up Environment Variables**
    JWT_SECRET=<your-jwt-secret>
    MONGODB_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/ # Local MongoDB or cloud
    PORT=3000

## **Start the server**
    npm start
    The server will run on http://localhost:3000 by default.










heroku deployment  "git push heroku Feature/webSocket:main"
